tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control (diabetes). Cholesterol, triglycerides, and chloride are mildly elevated, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk and possible mild electrolyte imbalance. Renal function and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend review of diabetes and lipid management, and monitoring of cardiovascular risk factors.
